==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Goethite
<hw>Goe"thite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After the
poet <etsep>G⟦oum⟧the</etsep>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A hydrous
oxide of iron (<chform>HFeO2</chform>), occurring in prismatic crystals,
also massive, with a fibrous, reniform, or stalactitic structure. The
color varies from yellowish to blackish brown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

